HEADWORD: Permeability
<hw>Per`me*a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>perm⟦eacute⟧abilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state
of being permeable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Magnetic permeability</b></col> <fld>(Physics)</fld>,
<cd>the specific capacity of a body for magnetic induction, or its
conducting power for lines of magnetic force.</cd> <rj><au>Sir W.
Thomson.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Permeable</ent>⟦br⟧
